		"\0\s[1]Sometimes I wonder what it would have been like to have been born the Shrine Guardian of a different Ace... \s[0]surely I would have turned out similar?.. \n\w9\w9\s[3]...Or perhaps my studies of Alonai'a have sculpted me more than I give them credit for...\s[1]\n I am thankful for how it all worked out."
		
		"\0\s[0]Ah, being here in the shrine reminds me...once, while I was away from home, a little lost Kikuminu snuck its way into my house. The little fellow must have been starving; by the time I got home, he had nearly chewed through my entire supply of dried meats!\n\n \w9...I don't mind. He needed the food more than I did. I can only hope he got back home, safe and warm."

		"\0\s[1]Brrrr, it's a bit chilly in here... \s[0]when I'm at home, it's easy to stay warm, but here at the shrine it gets a bit nippy.\n\w9\s[1]...The marble floors are pretty, but they're not so great for retaining heat..."

		"\0\s[1]I'm lucky the architects of the temple decided to put a nice, big hearth here... I'm not sure what I'd do if there was no place to brew a pot of tea. \w9\w9\w2 \n\s[0]...Er, \s[3]on second thought, \s[1]this may have been placed here primarily for ceremonies, \s[0]not personal pleasure.\n\n \w9\s[1]...Oh well. Haha!"

		"\0\s[0]I have always loved how sound echoes in here. When I was younger, I brought my flute with me and let its songs ring out through the stone hallways...\w7 ah, perhaps I should dust it off and learn to play it again."
		
		"\0\s[0]I'm looking forward to getting back home and being able to sleep in my own bed... \s[1]the shrine's little cot isn't very comfortable. \s[0]It makes me feel thankful for my comfortable little nest back home, so perhaps it keeps me humble...\n\n \s[1]...Though, my spine doesn't appreciate the 'humbling' very much!"
		
		"\0\s[1]The other shrines have been through their fair share of renovations, but I've never really thought to upgrade the temple... \s[0]perhaps it is the historian in me, but I would rather preserve the ancient beauty of the original temple, even if renovations would add to its practical capabilities...\n\n \s[1]Hmm... is it the 'historian' in me, \s[1]or the 'old geezer?' Who's to say... \s[1]haha!"
		
		"\0\s[3]I think I underpacked when I left from home... \s[0]I only packed three instant lunches. Not nearly enough for breakfast, lunch, and dinner for two days!.. \s[1]Oh well. I'll have to scrounge around in the private room of the temple, see if my students left any food for me. \s[0]They know I'm a bit forgetful with my food nowadays..."
		
		"\0\s[0]I found a few %(food.adj) %(root)s in my bag... could be useful as a midnight snack, if I don't feel like leaving the temple to get food in Welakaono! \s[1]Oh, on that note... do let me know if you get hungry, %(oomf)..! \s[0]I may be scrounging around in my bag for scraps, but I'll make sure you're fed... \s[1]haha!"
		
		if Flag("claris") == 1 && Flag("gio") == 1 && Flag ("inola") == 1
		{
			//all
